  "mermaid": "graph TD\n    Start([Oxidative Stress Response]) --> A1{Type of oxidative stress?}\n    \n    A1 -->|Hydrogen peroxide H2O2| A2[OxyR pathway activated]\n    A1 -->|Superoxide O2-| A3[SoxRS pathway activated]\n    A1 -->|Both| A4[Both pathways activated]\n    \n    A2 --> A5[H2O2 enters cell - diffuses across membrane]\n    A5 --> A6[Basal OxyR present as tetramer]\n    A6 --> A7[OxyR in reduced state - Cys199 Cys208 as thiols]\n    \n    A7 --> A8[H2O2 oxidizes Cys199]\n    A8 --> A9[Intramolecular disulfide bond forms Cys199-Cys208]\n    A9 --> A10[OxyR conformational change to activated state]\n    \n    A10 --> A11[Oxidized OxyR binds DNA at OxyR boxes]\n    A11 --> A12[OxyR activates transcription of ~30 genes]\n    \n    A12 --> A13{Which OxyR target genes?}\n    A13 -->|katG| A14[/Catalase KatG - degrades H2O2 to H2O + O2/]\n    A13 -->|ahpCF| A15[Alkyl hydroperoxide reductase AhpC - reduces H2O2 and organic peroxides]\n    A13 -->|gor| A16[Glutathione reductase - regenerates reduced glutathione]\n    A13 -->|dps| A17[DNA-binding protein Dps - protects DNA from oxidation]\n    A13 -->|grxA| A18[Glutaredoxin - reduces disulfides]\n    A13 -->|oxyS| A19[Small RNA OxyS - post-transcriptional regulation]\n    \n    A14 --> A20[H2O2 detoxification]\n    A15 --> A20\n    A16 --> A21[Thiol homeostasis restored]\n    A17 --> A22[DNA protected from damage]\n    A18 --> A21\n    A19 --> A23[Downregulates RpoS and other targets]\n    \n    A20 --> A24{H2O2 levels decreased?}\n    A24 -->|Yes| A25[Glutaredoxin or glutathione reduces OxyR disulfide]\n    A24 -->|No - high stress| A26[Maintain high OxyR activity]\n    \n    A25 --> A27[OxyR returns to reduced inactive state]\n    A27 --> A28[Transcription of OxyR regulon decreases]\n    \n    A3 --> A30[Superoxide O2- generated intracellularly]\n    A30 --> A31[\"Sources: respiratory chain, redox cycling drugs\"]\n    \n    A31 --> A32[Basal SoxR present as homodimer]\n    A32 --> A33[SoxR contains (\\1) cluster per monomer]\n    \n    A33 --> A34[Superoxide oxidizes (\\1) cluster]\n    A34 --> A35[\"One-electron oxidation (\\1)+ to (\\1)2+\"]\n    A35 --> A36[Oxidized SoxR conformational change]\n    \n    A36 --> A37[SoxR binds soxS promoter with higher affinity]\n    A37 --> A38[SoxR activates soxS transcription]\n    \n    A38 --> A39[SoxS protein synthesized]\n    A39 --> A40[SoxS belongs to AraC family transcription factors]\n    \n    A40 --> A41[SoxS binds soxboxes in promoters]\n    A41 --> A42[SoxS activates transcription of ~100 genes]\n    \n    A42 --> A43{Which SoxS target genes?}\n    A43 -->|sodA| A44[Manganese superoxide dismutase SodA - O2- to H2O2]\n    A43 -->|nfo| A45[Endonuclease IV - repairs oxidized DNA]\n    A43 -->|acrAB| A46[AcrAB efflux pump - exports toxic compounds]\n    A43 -->|zwf| A47[Glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase - NADPH production]\n    A43 -->|fumC| A48[Fumarase C - resistant to superoxide]\n    A43 -->|micF| A49[Small RNA MicF - downregulates OmpF]\n    \n    A44 --> A50[Superoxide detoxification - produces H2O2]\n    A45 --> A51[DNA damage repair]\n    A46 --> A52[Export of redox-cycling compounds]\n    A47 --> A53[NADPH for reducing power]\n    A48 --> A54[Maintain TCA cycle under stress]\n    A49 --> A55[Reduce outer membrane permeability]\n    \n    A50 --> A56{Superoxide eliminated?}\n    A56 -->|Yes - H2O2 produced| A57[H2O2 triggers OxyR pathway]\n    A56 -->|No - persistent stress| A58[Maintain SoxRS activity]\n    \n    A57 --> A2\n    \n    A58 --> A59[Continued SoxS synthesis]\n    A59 --> A60{SoxS half-life very short ~10 min}\n    A60 -->|Stress persists| A61[Continuous transcription needed]\n    A60 -->|Stress relieved| A62[/SoxS rapidly degraded by Lon protease/]\n    \n    A61 --> A42\n    A62 --> A63[SoxR returns to reduced state]\n    A63 --> A64[SoxS regulon turned off]\n    \n    A4 --> A65[Coordinate response to mixed oxidants]\n    A65 --> A66[OxyR and SoxRS regulons overlap]\n    A66 --> A67{Overlapping genes?}\n    A67 -->|fumC| A68[Activated by both pathways - additive]\n    A67 -->|ahpCF| A69[Activated by both - synergistic]\n    \n    A68 --> A70[Maximum protection]\n    A69 --> A70\n    \n    A20 --> A71[Cell survival under oxidative stress]\n    A50 --> A71\n    A51 --> A71\n    A52 --> A71\n    A53 --> A71\n    \n    A71 --> End1([Protected from oxidative damage])\n    A28 --> End2([Return to basal state])\n    A64 --> End2\n    \n    A26 --> A72[Chronic oxidative stress adaptation]\n    A72 --> A73[Sustained gene expression]\n    A73 --> A74[\"Alternative: mutagenesis if severe\"]\n    A74 --> End3([Adaptation or death])\n    \n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n    style A1 fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style A2 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A3 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A4 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A5 fill:#000000,color:#fff\n    style A6 fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style A7 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A8 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A9 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A10 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A11 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A12 fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style A13 fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style A14 fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff\n    style A15 fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style A16 fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style A17 fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style A18 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A19 fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style A20 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A21 fill:#000000,color:#fff\n    style A22 fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style A23 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A24 fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style A25 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A26 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A27 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A28 fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style A30 fill:#000000,color:#fff\n    style A31 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A32 fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style A33 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A34 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A35 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A36 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A37 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A38 fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style A39 fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style A40 fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style A41 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A42 fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style A43 fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style A44 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A45 fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style A46 fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style A47 fill:#000000,color:#fff\n    style A48 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A49 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A50 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A51 fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style A52 fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style A53 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A54 fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style A55 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A56 fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style A57 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A58 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A59 fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style A60 fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style A61 fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style A62 fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff\n    style A63 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A64 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A65 fill:#000000,color:#fff\n    style A66 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A67 fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style A68 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A69 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A70 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A71 fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style A72 fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style A73 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style A74 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000",
  "name": "Oxidative Stress Response (OxyR and SoxRS)",
  "notGates": 2,
  "notes": "Oxidative stress response demonstrates elegant dual pathway architecture where OxyR responds to H2O2 and SoxRS to superoxide, with overlapping regulons providing comprehensive protection. The OxyR mechanism (cysteine oxidation forming disulfide) is a paradigm for redox sensing. SoxR's Fe-S cluster oxidation represents a different sensing mechanism. These pathways are highly conserved and essential for aerobic life. Superoxide from SodA generates H2O2, creating cross-talk between pathways. This system has medical relevance as oxidative stress defense is critical for pathogen survival in hosts.",
  "organism": "E. coli",
  "relatedProcesses": [
    "ecoli_heat_shock_response",
    "ecoli_sos_response",
    "ecoli_envelope_stress_response",
    "ecoli_base_excision_repair"
  ],
  "scientificAccuracy": "This flowchart is based on extensive genetic and biochemical characterization of E. coli oxidative stress responses. All regulatory proteins (OxyR, SoxR, SoxS), sensing mechanisms (cysteine oxidation, Fe-S cluster oxidation), target genes, and protective functions have been validated through decades of research. The model represents the paradigm for bacterial oxidative stress defense.",
